# AI System Rules

## Responsibility

Ensure AI mentor / agent behavior is specified, bounded, and evaluable.

## Preconditions

AI features need explicit AI behavior requirements in Specifications (allowed / forbidden / evaluation).

## Practice

- Prefer deterministic evaluation hooks for critical teaching claims
- Separate product behavior specs from prompt/config implementation details
- Log/eval strategy must respect privacy constraints in Specs
- Document model/provider choices via ADR when selected

## Forbidden

- Unbounded autonomous actions without Spec guardrails
- Inventing pedagogical claims not backed by Product/Spec
- Exfiltrating user data into prompts without privacy review
- Treating prompt files as a substitute for Specifications
